<p>As a Principal, Chris serves as the primary point of client contact during our engagements.  
His responsibilities vary by project but typically include project management and both architectural 
and development leadership roles.  Chris has the ability to understand our client's business goals, create a list 
of project requirements, translate these requirements into the language of developers and lead the development effort.</p>
<p>Chris Collier came to Nevo from British Telecom Inc. in 2005 to lead front-end development of the Rightsphere project at Copyright Clearance Center.</p>
<p>He has since provided technical leadership on several Nevo projects, working at all levels of the technology stack.  Chris employs a "player/coach" leadership style: working as one of the development team while providing mentor ship to more junior members and lending a sensitive ear to clients' needs.</p>
<p>With a passion for computing and broad experience in many software development environments, Chris functions as a versatile and well-rounded member of any software development team.</p>
Chris holds an M.S. in Computer Science from Tufts University and a B.A. in Architecture from Connecticut College.

